messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
Can you hear me? Can you hear me?
Yes, I can hear you. What's going on?
Okay, 25 Arch Street, apartment four. You know what I'm talking about?
Okay, what's going on?
Hello? What's going on at 25 South Arch, apartment four?
Well, I just strangled my girlfriend.
You strangled your girlfriend?
Yep.
What's your name?
Randy.
Randy?
Yeah.
Okay, where are you at right now?
I'm sitting here on the bed, getting ready to go out by the door.
You're getting ready to go out by the door?
Yeah.
Okay, what are you wearing?
I got a walker. I can't walk well.
So you want me to stay on the phone or stay right in here or what?
I don't... Where are you at? You're just standing by the door? You're in her apartment?
I'm in her apartment right now. I'm on the edge of the bed.
What's her name?
Willa, Taylor, Helman.
Alright. So we got them coming to you.
Okay.
Do you have any weapons?
No, I don't. Nope.
Okay. I want you to stay on the line with me, okay? You're sure you're at 25 South Arch, apartment four?
Yes.
I need to get up and unlock the door.
Okay. Do you see the officers?
Pardon me?
Do you see the officers?
No, I'm sitting on the bed. I need to walk over to the door to unlock it.
Okay, go ahead and unlock the door.
He advised he is in a walker and having difficulty walking at this time.
Can you come out to the door right now?
Yes.
You're coming out right now?
Yes.
Do you have a cordless phone?
Pardon me?
Are you on a cordless phone?
I have a cordless phone, but I use a walker.
You can go ahead and hang up with me and go ahead out.
All right. Bye.
Bye.
